00:05:59.129 --> 00:06:03.270
and hungry. And then, hunger itself reduced
the amount of available food by diminishing

00:06:03.270 --> 00:06:09.279
people's capacity to work, since a decrease
from 2,500 to 2,000 calories halves our ability

00:06:09.279 --> 00:06:14.699
to work efficiently because the body's basic
metabolism still requires 1,500 calories.

00:06:14.699 --> 00:06:19.029
And hungry people are also more susceptible
to disease. Add together floods, droughts,

00:06:19.029 --> 00:06:23.080
harvest failures, and disease, and you get
a vicious cycle leading to population decline,

00:06:23.080 --> 00:06:26.149
which is exactly what happened in the seventeenth
century.

00:06:26.149 --> 00:06:30.189
Thanks, Thought Bubble. So, all of that is
pretty horrible, but human suffering in the

00:06:30.189 --> 00:06:34.679
seventeenth century wasn't just caused by
cold and drought. There was also a lot of

00:06:34.679 --> 00:06:39.669
war going on. And these wars between and within
states multiplied the effects of hunger as

00:06:39.669 --> 00:06:44.520
soldiers looted wherever they went. Like the
Chinese even coined a word for soldiers' bad

00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:50.580
behavior: binghuo, which means "soldier calamity".
And then, to add injury to injury, the costs

00:06:50.580 --> 00:06:55.369
of most of these wars were borne by the peasants,
who suffered doubly as their taxes went to

00:06:55.369 --> 00:07:00.289
pay for the king's wars, which brought soldier
calamity. These taxes were often on staples

00:07:00.289 --> 00:07:05.309
like bread, and so they often led to bread
riots, which were not great for morale.

00:07:05.309 --> 00:07:10.779
And yes, terrible weather could even contribute
to the fall of dynasties. The 1641 drought

00:07:10.779 --> 00:07:16.409
in China was so bad that the Grand Canal began
to dry up for the only time in history, which

00:07:16.409 --> 00:07:20.499
reduced rice shipments to China's capitol.
Unable to feed the people, the Ming emperor

00:07:20.499 --> 00:07:25.889
surrendered to the Qing in 1644. Drought and
cold had also encouraged the Qing to overthrow

00:07:25.889 --> 00:07:30.149
the Ming in the first place as poor harvests
in Manchuria convinced their leaders that

00:07:30.149 --> 00:07:35.349
invading China was the only way to avoid catastrophe.
And then the Qing got to China and they were

00:07:35.349 --> 00:07:38.899
like, "Where's all your food?" and they were
like, "Yeah, the whole planet is colder, not

00:07:38.899 --> 00:07:42.199
just Korea." But then they were already there
so they decided to have a dynasty for a while.

00:07:42.199 --> 00:07:43.610
I am your history teacher.

00:07:43.610 --> 00:07:47.309
So, obviously, protests and rebellions were
public responses to the hunger and war, but

00:07:47.309 --> 00:07:51.479
many people confronted the problem of hunger
by trying to reduce the number of mouths they

00:07:51.479 --> 00:07:55.770
had to feed. They could do this by reducing
the number of births through postponed marriage

00:07:55.770 --> 00:08:00.300
or, in more extreme cases, through infanticide.
And the most desperate resorted to suicide.

00:08:00.300 --> 00:08:04.909
Now, we don't have many records of suicide
rates, but a Qing decree of 1688 forbidding

00:08:04.909 --> 00:08:08.439
